wikipedia_page.main: Agnes Alice Beckwith (24 August 1861 – 10 July 1951) was an English swimmer

response: Davies is the author of six novels; Jamestown Blues (1996), Black Mulberries (2008), Friends Like Us (2009), The Ghost of Lily Painter (2011) a fictionalised account of two Edwardian baby farmers who were hanged at Holloway Prison in 1903, Family Likeness (2013) which draws on the experiences of mixed race UK children born to African-American soldiers during World War Two, as well as the story of Dido Elizabeth Belle, Britain's "first black aristocrat". Daisy Belle: Swimming Champion of the World, based on the life of Agnes Beckwith, was published in 2018.
